==English==

===Verb===
'''[[do]] one's [[darnedest]]'''
#{{idiom}} {{euphemism}} To do one's [[utmost]]; to make every [[effort]] or to try every possible approach or way.
#:''I don't think he'll succeed, but he's '''doing his darnedest''' to build a working spaceship.''

